    "\n",
    "### Question 1\n",
    "\n",

    "# Define parameters for Archimedes spiral, r = a + b theta\n",
    "a = 0.0\n",
    "b = 1./2*np.pi\n",
    "theta = np.linspace(0,6*np.pi)\n",
    "r = a + b*theta\n",
    "plt.polar(theta,r)"
   ]
  },

   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Question 4"
   ]

    "a_log = 2\n",
    "b_log = 0.18\n",
    "r_log = a_log*np.exp(b_log*theta)\n",
    "plt.polar(theta,r_log)"

   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Differentiation"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def forwardFD(fun,x,dx):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Calculate first order finite-difference of given function\n",
    "    Inputs:\n",
    "    fun (function to be differentiated)\n",
    "    x   \n",
    "    dx  (finite difference)\n",
    "    Returns:\n",
    "    finite difference\"\"\"\n",
    "    df = fun(x + dx) - fun(x)\n",
    "    return df/dx"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "x = 1.0\n",
    "N = 12\n",
    "dx_array = np.logspace(-N,-1,N)\n",
    "results = np.zeros(N)\n",
    "for i, dx in enumerate(dx_array):\n",
    "    results[i] = abs(forwardFD(np.sin,x,dx) - np.cos(1.0))\n",
    "plt.loglog(dx_array,results)\n",
    "plt.grid(True,':')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('dx')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Error')\n",
    "plt.title('Accuracy of FD approach')\n",
    "plt.grid(True, alpha=0.7, linestyle=':', which='both', axis='both')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def centredFD(fun,x,dx):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Calculate centred first order finite-difference of given function\n",
    "    Inputs:\n",
    "    fun (function to be differentiated)\n",
    "    x   \n",
    "    dx  (finite difference)\n",
    "    Returns:\n",
    "    finite difference\"\"\"\n",
    "    df = fun(x + dx) - fun(x - dx)\n",
    "    return df/(2*dx)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",

   "source": [
    "x = 1.0\n",
    "N = 12\n",
    "dx_array = np.logspace(-N,-1,N)\n",
    "results = np.zeros(N)\n",
    "for i, dx in enumerate(dx_array):\n",
    "    results[i] = abs(centredFD(np.sin,x,dx) - np.cos(1.0))\n",
    "plt.loglog(dx_array,results)\n",
    "plt.grid(True,':')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('dx')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Error')\n",
    "plt.title('Accuracy of centred FD approach')\n",
    "plt.grid(True, alpha=0.7, linestyle=':', which='both', axis='both')"
   ]

    "## 5. Integration\n",
    "\n",
    "### Question 1"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def rectangle_int(f,a,b,N):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Implement integration using rectangle rule\n",
    "    Inputs:\n",
    "    f    (function to be integrated)\n",
    "    a, b (limits in integration)\n",
    "    N    (number of points)\n",
    "    Returns value of integral\"\"\"\n",
    "    integral= 0.0\n",
    "    dx = (b-a)/N\n",
    "    for i in range(N):\n",
    "        integral += f(a+i*dx)\n",
    "    integral *= dx\n",
    "    return integral"
   ]
  },

   "metadata": {},
   "source": [

    "def dfx(x):\n",

   "source": [
    "def trapezium_int(f,a,b,N):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Implement integration using trapezium rule\n",
    "    Inputs:\n",
    "    f    (function to be integrated)\n",
    "    a, b (limits in integration)\n",
    "    N    (number of points)\n",
    "    Returns value of integral\"\"\"\n",
    "    # End points\n",
    "    integral= 0.5 * (f(a) + f(b))\n",
    "    dx = (b-a)/N\n",
    "    for i in range(1,N): # We want to go to N-1\n",
    "        integral += f(a+i*dx)\n",
    "    integral *= dx\n",
    "    return integral"
   ]
